./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:1:# PRD: Home Resilience — Durable State, Safe Reboot, and Recovery
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:82:- Queue DB: `/home/user/cypherclaw/.sdp/state.db`
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:83:- Observatory DB: `/home/user/cypherclaw/.promptclaw/observatory.db`
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:84:- Tmpfs root: `/run/cypherclaw-tmp/`
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:88:- Daemon service: `cypherclaw.service`
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:94:| HOME-001 | Make the live queue DB authoritative on disk. `sdp.toml` must point to the persistent disk path for `state.db`, and no reboot/bootstrap path may replace the live disk DB with a tmpfs copy. | MUST | T1 | - Live queue authority is `/home/user/cypherclaw/.sdp/state.db`<br/>- Reboot preserves queue counts without reconstruction<br/>- `tools/init_workdir.sh` no longer promotes tmpfs DB copies over disk authority |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:95:| HOME-002 | Make the Observatory DB authoritative on disk and explicitly preserve it across reboot. Tmpfs may cache reads or logs, but not replace observatory authority. | MUST | T1 | - Live observatory authority is `/home/user/cypherclaw/.promptclaw/observatory.db`<br/>- Reboot preserves observatory row counts and WAL integrity<br/>- Bootstrap does not create a fresh empty authoritative observatory DB |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:99:| HOME-006 | Create `cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service` and move `sdp-cli run` under systemd. The queue runner must no longer rely on `nohup`, ad hoc shells, or manual restart. | MUST | T1 | - Runner starts via `systemctl start cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service`<br/>- `Restart=always` is enabled so clean `sdp-cli run` exits do not leave the queue dead<br/>- Maintenance-mode launcher exits do not restart-loop (`SuccessExitStatus=75`, `RestartPreventExitStatus=75`)<br/>- Logs are journaled and visible without tailing a custom shell log<br/>- Reboot restores runner under ordered startup |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-home-resilience.md:100:| HOME-007 | Create a dedicated bootstrap layer for tmpfs and workdir prep. Add `cypherclaw-bootstrap.service` to initialize caches, workdirs, and symlinks without owning the authority DBs. | MUST | T1 | - Bootstrap runs before daemon and runner<br/>- tmpfs directories exist after boot<br/>- bootstrap is idempotent<br/>- bootstrap never downgrades live DB state |
