./sdp/verification/t-002@20260425t183959za-verify.md:41:**Minor note:** `writeDefFile("synthdefs/")` is a relative path. When sclang is invoked from the repo root (as suggested in the SC-side test header comment), this resolves to `./synthdefs/sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` (repo root) rather than `synthesis/synthdefs/sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef`. The SC-side test assertion (a) checks `~defPath = "my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef"` — this path **will not match** the actual output when launched from the repo root. The Python test only checks the string is present; it cannot catch the path mismatch. This will cause SC-side test assertion (a) to fail on cypherclaw unless sclang is invoked from within `synthesis/`.
