./sdp/verification/t-031-verify.md:20:The output matches the requirements. A broad grep search for "viewer", "listener", and "count" patterns across the entire composer source tree (`my-claw/tools/senseweave/`, `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`, and `src/cypherclaw/`) confirms that no audience size or telemetry signals are consumed. The only "audience" related variable is `audience_attention` (derived from `attention_score`), which represents physical presence in the room, not a remote viewer/listener count.
