sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:67:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:45:43.906Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777178743714_0","status":"success","output":"commit 0345b299714d30cb3f1f7c480fa9eb4edccad83d (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation)\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 21:44:14 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(sampler): add post-piece hook that writes usage journal entries [T-022@20260425T183959Zc]\n    \n    Adds `post_piece_hook(tracker, arc_payoff_score, journal_path)` and\n    `derive_arc_payoff_summary(...)` to `senseweave.usage_journal`. The hook\n    consumes the active `SampleUsageTracker`, derives a banded textual\n    arc-payoff summary (weak/moderate/strong + score + sample count), folds\n    the accumulated plays into a `JournalEntry`, and appends it to the\n    journal file. Tests cover summary banding, hook invocation + on-disk\n    output, multi-piece appends, and the no-active-piece error path.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py | 37 +++++++++++++\n tests/test_usage_journal.py               | 86 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n 2 files changed, 123 insertions(+)\n\ncommit 0c669c41b536a2da7efc4ba7b275c2abeb647e04\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 21:39:58 2026 -0700\n\n    verify(T-022@20260425T183959Zb): PASS — SampleUsageTracker accumulation verified\n\n progress.md                                        | 18 ++++++++-----\n sdp/notifications.log                              | 13 ++++++++++\n sdp/run-log.md                                     | 14 +++++++++-\n sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959zb-verify.md | 30 ++++++++++++++++++++++\n 4 files changed, 67 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)\n\ncommit b8b3ac70ea647da0cf52994639bf428e55ff611b\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 21:38:14 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(sampler): add SampleUsageTracker for piece playback [T-022@20260425T183959Zb]\n    \n    Accumulate sample plays (id, transposition, fx preset, trigger row) during\n    piece playback into a JournalEntry ready for append_to_journal.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py |  65 ++++++++++-\n tests/test_usage_journal.py               | 183 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-\n 2 files changed, 245 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n\ncommit 68a2f6d923ce9a87e2e3fc0b52a7e13b58378d59\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 21:33:58 2026 -0700\n\n    verify(T-022@20260425T183959Za): PASS WITH NOTES — journal schema and serialization tests verified\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959za-verify.md | 53 ++++++++++++++++++++++\n 1 file changed, 53 insertions(+)\n\ncommit f33edf8c611f0424b218589e2f28ca565b4b097f\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 21:31:29 2026 -0700\n\n    fix(sampler): define usage journal schema and write tests [T-022@20260425T183959Za]\n\n my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py | 55 +++++++++++++++++\n tests/test_usage_journal.py               | 98 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n 2 files changed, 153 insertions(+)"}
sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:82:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:46:01.807Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777178761807_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-022@20260425T183959Zc\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py`\n- `tests/test_usage_journal.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\n- `tests/test_first_boot.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly wires the `post_piece_hook` as requested. It consumes the `SampleUsageTracker` state, derives a textual arc-payoff summary based on the provided score and sample count, and appends a `JournalEntry` to the storage file. The textual summary banding logic (weak/moderate/strong) is correctly implemented and formatted.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation handles all required scenarios:\n- Textual summary rendering with score and count.\n- Hook invocation that correctly resets the tracker state.\n- Durability via `os.fsync` in `append_to_journal` (which was pre-existing but utilized here).\n- Multi-piece append behavior.\n- Error handling when no active piece is tracked (raises `RuntimeError`).\nComprehensive tests cover all these paths.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established patterns in the `usage_journal` module and matches the `JournalEntry` and `SampleUsageTracker` abstractions landed in previous subtasks (Za/Zb). The use of `Path` objects and type hints is consistent with the project's standards.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The journal storage uses a configurable path that defaults to `samples/usage_journal.jsonl`. No sensitive information is logged or stored.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, modular, and well-tested. The `derive_arc_payoff_summary` function is properly isolated and tested. The hook function is documented and returns the created entry for easy inspection/logging by callers.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] (Resolved) Mandatory hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were verified as pre-existing and correctly wired in the daemon startup flow.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and satisfies all requirements for T-022 Zc. The integration with the existing tracker and journal persistence layers is seamless. The hardening anchors for startup identity were also verified as passing.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-022 @20260425t183959zc-verify.md"}}
